author: COMSOL
description:
This example demonstrates the forced vibration analysis of a composite laminate under bending and twisting loads. The composite laminate considered for this analysis is made of carbon–epoxy material and has three layers with angle-ply layup.

This model computes the structural impedance as a function of frequency at various positions. The effect of different types of delamination on the structural impedance is also analyzed. The presence of delamination is the modeled using the Layerwise (LW) theory of modeling composite laminates.
